        <element name="Draconic Bloodline" type="Archetype Feature" source="Order of the Dragon" id="ID_DM_OOTD_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_OOT_DRAGON_DRACONIC_BLOODLINE">
            <description>
                <p>Starting at 3rd level, once you have chosen this archetype, your draconic bloodline begins to manifest changes in you. You may either choose your draconic bloodline or roll a d10 to have the fates determine your ancestry for you. The damage type associated with each dragon earns the associated Primal Rite, and is used by features you gain later.</p>
                <p class="indent">These primal rites will grant you powerful elemental control that will expand outward from you while your crimson rite is active. When your crimson rite causes a creature to make a save, the save DC is:</p>
                <center>
                    <p><strong>Rite Save DC</strong> = 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Constitution modifier.</p>
                </center>
                <p class="indent">The options presented in the list above introduce the possibility of learning two rites that were previously not available:</p>
                <p><strong>Rite of the Acrid.</strong> Your rite damage is acid type.</p>
                <p><strong>Rite of the Venomous.</strong> Your rite damage is poison type.</p>
                <table>
                    <thead>
                        <tr><td>d10</td><td>Dragon</td><td>Primal Rite</td><td>Damage Type</td></tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tr><td>1</td><td>Black</td><td>Acrid</td><td>Acid</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>2</td><td>Blue</td><td>Storm</td><td>Lightning</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>3</td><td>Brass</td><td>Flame</td><td>Fire</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>4</td><td>Bronze</td><td>Storm</td><td>Lightning</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>5</td><td>Copper</td><td>Acrid</td><td>Acid</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>6</td><td>Gold</td><td>Flame</td><td>Fire</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>7</td><td>Green</td><td>Venomous</td><td>Poison</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>8</td><td>Red</td><td>Flame</td><td>Fire</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>9</td><td>Silver</td><td>Frozen</td><td>Cold</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>10</td><td>White</td><td>Frozen</td><td>Cold</td></tr>
                </table>
            </description>
            <sheet>
                <description>When your crimson rite causes a creature to make a save, the save DC is: {{rite:save-dc}}.</description>
            </sheet>
            <rules>
                <stat name="rite:save-dc" value="8" />
                <stat name="rite:save-dc" value="proficiency" />
                <stat name="rite:save-dc" value="constitution:modifier" />
                <select type="Archetype Feature" name="Draconic Bloodline" supports="Order of the Dragon Bloodline" />
            </rules>
        </element>
