        <element name="Rending Claws" type="Archetype Feature" source="Order of the Dragon" id="ID_DM_OOTD_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_OOT_DRAGON_RENDING_CLAWS">
            <description>
                <p>Upon reaching 7th level, your mastery over your crimson rite greatly increases the power of your unarmed strikes. When you have an active rite, your unarmed strikes are considered magical for the purpose of overcoming resistance and immunity to nonmagical attacks and damage.</p>
                <p class="indent">Your draconic power can be channeled to rend the very flesh from your opponent’s bones. When you roll a critical hit with your unarmed strikes and your active rite is that of your draconic bloodline, you can roll one additional crimson rite die when determining the extra damage for the critical hit.</p>
            </description>
            <sheet>
                <description>When you have an active rite, your unarmed strikes are considered magical for the purpose of overcoming resistance and immunity to nonmagical attacks and damage. When you roll a critical hit with your unarmed strikes and your active rite is that of your draconic bloodline, you can roll one additional crimson rite die when determining the extra damage for the critical hit.</description>
            </sheet>
        </element>
        <element name="Crimson Rite Barrier" type="Archetype Feature" source="Order of the Dragon" id="ID_DM_OOTD_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_OOT_DRAGON_CRIMSON_RITE_BARRIER">
            <description>
                <p>When you reach level 11, you learn how to channel your draconic bloodline’s power into a protective barrier that can bolster your defense.</p>
                <p class="indent">When you take damage from a creature within 10 feet of you, you can use your reaction to reduce the damage from the chosen creature by half.</p>
            </description>
            <sheet action="Reaction">
                <description>When you take damage from a creature within 10 feet of you, you can use your reaction to reduce the damage from the chosen creature by half.</description>
            </sheet>
        </element>
        <element name="Hemorrhaging Critical" type="Archetype Feature" source="Order of the Dragon" id="ID_DM_OOTD_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_OOT_DRAGON_HEMORRHAGING_CRITICAL">
            <description>
                <p>Upon reaching 15th level, your claw attacks wound in the most grievous manner. Whenever you score a critical hit on an attack with your unarmed strikes, the target additionally suffers half of the damage from the attack at the end of its next turn.</p>
            </description>
            <sheet>
                <description>Whenever you score a critical hit on an attack with your unarmed strikes, the target additionally suffers half of the damage from the attack at the end of its next turn.</description>
            </sheet>
        </element>
        <element name="Dragonkin" type="Archetype Feature" source="Order of the Dragon" id="ID_DM_OOTD_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_OOT_DRAGON_DRAGONKIN">
            <description>
                <p>At 18th level, you have mastered your control over your draconic form. You can focus your draconic bloodline’s rite into a powerful breath weapon. You gain the Blood Curse of the Dragonkin Blood Maledict feature. This does not count against your blood curses known.</p>
                <p class="indent"><strong><em>Blood Curse ofthe Dragonkin. (Recharge 5-6)</em></strong> You can choose to sacrifice your own vitality to weaponize your Crimson Rite to create a devastating breath weapon.</p>
                <p class="indent">As an Action, you exhale a destructive breath weapon as described in the Blood Curse of the Dragonkin table below. Each creature that lies within the area must make the appropriate saving throw as described or take 8d8 damage of the type associated with your draconic bloodline on a failure, or half damage on a success.</p>
                <p class="indent"><strong><em>Amplify.</em></strong> Your breath weapon ignores resistance to the damage type associated with your draconic bloodline.</p>
                </description>
            <sheet action="Action">
                <description>Blood Curse ofthe Dragonkin. (Recharge 5-6) As an Action, you exhale a destructive breath weapon in a {{draconic-bloodline:weapon-shape}}. Creatures within the area of effect must make a {{draconic-bloodline:weapon-save}} saving throw or take 8d8 {{draconic-bloodline:damage-type}} damage on a failure, or half damage on a success. Amplify: your breath weapon ignores resistance to {{draconic-bloodline:damage-type}}.</description>
            </sheet>
        </element>

